preference.name: TYPE_DISPLAY_RULES_list_types_of_subclasses
preference.preference_description: Preferences for Type Display Rules This is a site preference. For all the entries under this preference the user interface for Type Display Rule shows the types implemented by the subclasses too.

preference.name: ASSIGNED_ITEM_REV_MODIFIABLE
preference.preference_description: Determines whether an automatically generated Item revID can be modified by users after it has been generated. The default value is 0. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - When the item rev ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated item ID cannot be modified by the user. 1 - When the item rev ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated item ID can be modified by the user.

preference.name: ICS_classifiable_types
preference.preference_description: Identifies whether the particular type can be classified or not. It's recommended that this be set to Item/ItemRevision.

preference.name: TC_QRY_display_latest_dataset_only
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of only the latest version of dataset objects in results of queries with search class as super class of Dataset or its descendant classes (e.g. queries with search class as WorkspaceObject). Valid values are: 0 - to display all versions of the dataset (default value). 1 - to display only the latest version of dataset objects.

preference.name: HiddenPerspectives
preference.preference_description: Lists the Teamcenter perspectives to hide from the end-users. Valid values are the activity names as defined in the com.teamcenter.rac.activity's plugin.xml file.

preference.name: AE_dataset_default_keep_limit
preference.preference_description: Default number of versions of Teamcenter datasets to keep before deleting old versions. Changing the value will only affect datasets created after the value is changed.

preference.name: PSEPreciseColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used when displaying a precise BVR in PSE (defaulted to sea green). The value can be a standard supported string, an octal number or a hexadecimal number. The standard strings supported are "black", "white", "lightGray", "gray", "darkGray", "red", "pink", "orange", "yellow", "green", "magenta", "cyan" and "blue". Example for a hexadecimal number is #50b080 which represents "Sea Green".

preference.name: EPM_multiple_processes_targets
preference.preference_description: Enables/Disables multiple processes for same objects in the Workflow application. Valid values are: * ON: Enables Multiple processes. This is the default value. * OFF: Disables Multiple processes.

preference.name: CR_allow_alternate_procedures
preference.preference_description:
Manages the visibility of workflow templates in the "New Process" panel of the Workflow application in the rich client. Valid values are: * any : The "All" option is pre-selected in the "All/Assigned" radio button group, which means that all templates are listed. * Assigned: The "Assigned" option is pre-selected in the "All/Assigned" radio button group, which means that only the templates assigned to the group and selected target object type are listed. * none: The options "All/Assigned" are not visible. Furthermore, only the templates assigned to the group and selected target object type are displayed (behaviour similar to the "Assigned" option). When no templates are assigned for the target group/type, the displayed list is empty. If no object was selected when initiating the workflow, all the templates assigned to the group are listed. This is the default value.
Process templates assigned to a group and a target object type are defined through the "Process designer->Edit->Template Filter" command.

preference.name: WRKFLW_use_legacy_template_filter
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether to use the legacy Type and Group based Template Filter or the new Condition based Template Filter. Valid values are: * true: Use the legacy Type and Group based Template Filter. * false: Use the new Condition based Template Filter. This is the default value.

preference.name: TASK_MONITOR_SLEEP_TIME
preference.preference_description: Used to set the sleep time for the task monitor daemon. Sleep time should be an integer specifying the desired number of minutes. e.g. 30 for 30 minutes, 60 for 1 hour and 120 for 2 hours.

preference.name: TC_inbox_interval
preference.preference_description: How often to check the In-Box for new tasks (in minutes). 1 - Disable the checking. 0 - Check at the time of logging in. X - Check every X minutes.

preference.name: EPM_notify_url_format
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of client connection for URL generation by notify and CR-notify handlers. The valid values are "rich", "dhtml", "activeworkspace" and "none".

preference.name: CM_change_derivations
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of change to create from a given source type during the Derive Change process. The format for valid values is "source_type/derived_type", where: source_type is the type of change from which to derive change, and derived_type is the type of change which will be created. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: TC_current_role
preference.preference_description: Specifies if ACCESS MANAGER should strictly enforce object access based on the user's current role. Valid values are true/false. true - Strictly enforce object access based on user's current role. false - Perform access control as done in previous releases.

preference.name: TCDefaultKeepLimit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default keep limit for Sequences in Teamcenter. The given value is used to initialize the keep limit when a Business Object is created if no specific keep limit is defined using TCDefaultKeepLimitByType preference. For Sequences, the keep limit is defined as the number of sequences retained after a Check-In operation. This preference is not applicable to Datasets. AE_dataset_default_keep_limit preference is used to specify the number of Dataset versions retained with each Dataset. Valid values are positive integers greater than 0.

preference.name: TCDefaultKeepLimitByType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the keep limit for a specific Business Object in Teamcenter. For each entry, the keep limit is applicable for that Business Object and any Business Objects inheriting from it. An inherited value of keep limit may be overridden by specifying a keep limit for the inheriting Business Object. For Sequences, the keep limit is defined as the number of sequences retained after Check-In. Valid values are space delimited Business Object-integer pairs. For example, Business Object A 3 or MyBusinessObject 2.

preference.name: TC_NX_nonmaster_additional_forms
preference.preference_description: Lists the (additional Form) Named References (UGPART-BBOX, UGPART-MASSPR, and UGPART-ATTRIBUTES) which are to be included in the create/update from NX for specific NX Non-Master Dataset types (UGPART, UGALTREP, UGSCENARIO). Format for the values is: <NX Dataset-type-name>:<NamedRef-Name>. Eg. UGPART:UGPART-BBOX. This preference affects the behaviour of NX v18.0 and later versions only and irrelevant to the earlier versions. Also the Named Reference Forms considered here have nothing to do with the regular NXManager Unigraphics attribute synchronization. This is a Site Preference.

preference.name: BOMExcludeFromPackCheck
preference.preference_description: Allows the exclusion of find number from the BOMLine pack check. Valid values are 'seqno' and 'none'. Setting it to 'seqno' means that BOMLines with distinct find numbers can be packed.

preference.name: TC_show_open_in_nx_button
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the "Open in NX" button should be displayed in the Teamcenter Rich Client. Valid values are true/false. true - Displays the button. false - Does not display the button.

preference.name: TCAllowedChildTypes_GET6MfgPart
preference.preference_description: Defines the Item types permitted in GET Manufacturing Part structures (internal type name GET6MfgPart).This site preference is valid only when the TCEnforceSingleType preference has been set to false.

preference.name: TCAllowedChildTypes_GET6Project

preference.name: TCAllowedChildTypes_GET6ElectPart

preference.name: TCAllowedChildTypes_GET6MechPart
preference.preference_description: Defines the Item types permitted in GET Mechanical Part structures (internal type name GET6MechPart). This site preference is valid only when the TCEnforceSingleType preference has been set to false.

preference.name: TCAllowedChildTypes_GET6PLIST

preference.name: TC_NX_occ_default_qty_prevent_from_blank
preference.preference_description: Sets the default quantity as 1 for a new component(occurrence) created from NXManager. Valid values are yes/no. The default is 'no' and this puts the quantity field as blank. This is a site preference.

preference.name: UGMASTER_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. UGMASTER. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: DATASET_saveas_pattern
preference.preference_description: Specifies the pattern string consisting of literal text and the following tokens: ${UserText}, ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID}. Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern, where ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} match the item id and revision id of the owning item revision respectively, and ${UserText} matches any text in the original name. If the existing dataset names do not match the pattern, then the new dataset names will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A. If a dataset's existing name is "drawing-001234/B" then the name is said to 'match' against the pattern. Since the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, dataset name "fea-001234/B" would also match against the pattern. However, "drawing_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "drawing-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets would be saved as "drawing-002345/A" and "fea-002345/A". According to preference DATASET_saveas_allow_name_modification, the user may be allowed to modify these generated names. However, if DATASET_saveas_force_name_validation is true, the user-edited name is still required to match the pattern. The preferences DATASET_saveas_pattern, DATASET_saveas_allow_name_modification, DATASET_saveas_force_name_validation, DATASET_saveas_always_copy, DATASET_saveas_never_copy, DATASET_saveas_owner, DATASET_saveas_allow_duplicates are currently only used by USER_copied_datasets_details and USER_copied_dataset_name, and these are only currently called by NXManager Unigraphics.

preference.name: UGPART_saveas_pattern

Value may contain text and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID, RevisionID or UserText. Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset names do not match the pattern, then the new dataset names will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A. If a dataset's existing name is "drawing-001234/B" then the name is said to 'match' against the pattern. Since the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, dataset name "fea-001234/B" would also match against the pattern. However, "drawing_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "drawing-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets would be saved as "drawing-002345/A" and "fea-002345/A". This is a site preference.

Value may contain text and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID, RevisionID or UserText. Existing dataset name is expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset name does not match the pattern, then the new dataset name will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. However, "master_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "master-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the dataset would be saved as "master-002345/A". This is a site preference.

Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset names do not match the pattern, then the new dataset names will not follow this pattern. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets would be saved as "altrep-002345/A" and "fea-002345/A". This is a site preference.

preference.preference_description: 0 - Do not create the snapshot folder after Baseline Creation. 1 - Create snapshot folder after Baseline Creation.

preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0/1/2. 0 - Create an ImPrecise Baseline. 1 - Create a Precise Baseline. 2 - Do not allow users to choose precise/imprecise and always create precise

preference.name: Baseline_release_procedures

preference.name: AE_dataset_id_gen_by_type

preference.preference_description: Defines if the OS Mail functionality is available. This is a site preference. Valid values are true (default) or false. When the value is false, the value given to preference "Mail_server_name" is not taken into account.

preference.name: Mail_internal_mail_activated
preference.preference_description: Defines if Teamcenter internal mail functionality is available when using the "notify" Workflow Handler. Valid values are true or false (default). When the value is false, Teamcenter internal mail will not be sent to the user's Teamcenter mailbox. This is a site preference.

preference.name: Mail_server_charset
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Teamcenter mail server character set used to send OS mail.

preference.name: Mail_server_name
preference.preference_description: Information about the mail gateway server. This is a site preference. It can be set to either a mail server name or to a numeric IP address. The mail server name should be a machine running a send mail daemon. Leaving it as "your mail server machine" while the "Mail_OSMail_activated" preference is true may give you errors telling you to set this preference if you try to use the "Send" command.

preference.name: Mail_server_port
preference.preference_description: Sets the port number used by the SMTP mail server to send OS mail. This is a site preference. The default value is 25.

preference.name: TC_mail_interval
preference.preference_description: Indicates default value (in minutes) for Teamcenter to check for new mail every X minutes.

preference.name: JT_File_Excluded_Refsets
preference.preference_description: should be set with a list of reference set names that user does not wish to view in the PSE Portal Viewer (e.g. Empty).

preference.name: GET6MCNRevision_ItemRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation to be created when a Item Revision is pasted under a Change Item Revision. The specified relation becomes the default relation created between a Item Revision and the target Change Item Revision.

preference.name: PS_assume_legacy_transform_units
preference.preference_description: Indicates which units the legacy transforms are in. For customers using data all in inches or millimeters, the value should be set, respectively, to "Inches" and "Millimeters". Otherwise, "Unknown" should be set. Note that values are case sensitive.
